1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:06,280
If you can.

2
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:08,600
walk straight toward me.

3
00:00:08,720 --> 00:00:10,000
I’ll let you kiss me.

4
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:15,040
Idiot. How can you sleep
when you’re this dirty?

5
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:21,600
You don’t have anything to say, right?
Then I’m leaving.

6
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,320
Hey, what are you doing?

7
00:00:23,360 --> 00:00:25,800
Can’t I hug my girlfriend
because I miss her?

8
00:00:25,840 --> 00:00:27,080
You...

9
00:00:27,120 --> 00:00:29,320
Have you ever had naughty
thoughts about me?

10
00:00:29,560 --> 00:00:31,960
I’m having them right now.

11
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,200
Do you like it?

12
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,040
I like it the most.

13
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:50,960
What are you doing?

14
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:52,560
P’ Klao.

15
00:00:53,240 --> 00:00:55,160
What did you just call me?

16
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:58,880
I’m just calling you the same way Jiw does.

17
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:00,760
P’ Klao.

18
00:01:01,760 --> 00:01:03,960
Do you like it when I call you that?

19
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:06,800
I like it the most.

20
00:01:07,520 --> 00:01:09,720
It makes me feel like.

21
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:13,400
I have to take care of you and cherish you.

22
00:01:15,520 --> 00:01:19,200
Then if you call me P’ Klao.

23
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:21,960
I’ll call you...

24
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:24,640
Si.

25
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:26,480
Si.

26
00:01:27,640 --> 00:01:29,840
Why does it sound like...

27
00:01:29,880 --> 00:01:32,640
I’m still a kid who hasn’t grown up?

28
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:34,600
Like I’m a kid all the time.

29
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:37,560
That’s not it at all.

30
00:01:37,880 --> 00:01:39,960
It comes from...

31
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:42,160
Khunnoo Si.

32
00:01:43,759 --> 00:01:46,000
Well, that sounds a bit better.

33
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:48,240
P’ Klao.

34
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:49,800
Si.

35
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:51,039
P’ Klao.

36
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,440
Si.

37
00:01:52,479 --> 00:01:54,000
P’ Klao.

38
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,560
-Si.
-Si.

39
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:58,400
-P’ Klao.
-Si.

40
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,120
So...

41
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,560
Do you feel better now?

42
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,079
I...

43
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:31,480
I do feel better now.

44
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:33,160
Ever since I’ve been with you.

45
00:02:33,880 --> 00:02:34,960
But...

46
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:37,160
that thing...

47
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:38,960
well...

48
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,680
it’s okay.

49
00:02:42,079 --> 00:02:45,640
Whenever you feel ready.

50
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:47,520
you can tell me then.

51
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:50,120
Because we’ll be together for a long time.

52
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,360
Thank you.

53
00:02:56,640 --> 00:02:59,000
You understand me in every way.

54
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:05,920
Come on, let’s go.

55
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:09,240
I have somewhere to take you today.

56
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:12,040
It’s still early.

57
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:15,440
-Let me sleep a little longer.
-Oh, come on.

58
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:17,960
What early? It’s already late.

59
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:20,880
-Come on, get up and go shower.
-No, no.

60
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:23,960
You said you were going to shower, right?

61
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:28,000
Then go shower first.

62
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:30,280
Let me sleep a bit more.

63
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:31,800
Once you’re done.

64
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,640
I’ll go shower right away.

65
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:36,880
Fine, I’m not going.

66
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:39,480
If you don’t get up.

67
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:41,440
I’m going to...

68
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:43,280
Hey, P’.

69
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:45,280
Wasn’t two rounds last night enough?

70
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:47,000
Even ten wouldn’t be enough.

71
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:25,800
P’.

72
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:27,480
Let me put on your skincare.

73
00:06:27,960 --> 00:06:29,640
Can you help take a look for me?

74
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,120
So smooth.

75
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:04,040
Here?

76
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,880
The place you said you’d take me?

77
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:09,320
I saw you’ve been feeling uneasy.

78
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:11,720
So I brought you somewhere
for peace of mind.

79
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,160
Honestly.

80
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:17,560
It’s pretty peaceful here.

81
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:21,040
But normally, I don’t really go to temples.

82
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:23,760
Back in Bangkok, no one invites me.

83
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:25,960
And I don’t really have time.

84
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:29,320
You do have time, it’s just...

85
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:31,520
you spend it all shopping.

86
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:34,640
Let’s pray.

87
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:36,640
And make a wish.

88
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:39,200
for all the bad things
to be washed away.

89
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:00,800
Come to think of it.

90
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:02,880
After praying...

91
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:05,280
I do feel better.

92
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:07,640
If you like it.

93
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:09,520
I’ll bring you here more often.

94
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:14,400
You like praying, making merit,
and giving alms.

95
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,360
Then why don’t you just ordain?

96
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:19,840
It’s not that I want to ordain, but...

97
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:22,200
I’d rather press closer.

98
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:23,320
Press closer?

99
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:25,200
What are you talking about?

100
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:27,960
Back then.

101
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:30,400
when people were
getting married, elders would say.

102
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:32,320
you had to ordain first, then press close.

103
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:33,919
It means.

104
00:08:33,919 --> 00:08:36,799
I want to be closer to you.

105
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,760
Did you ever ask me.

106
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:41,640
if I want to be close to you?

107
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:46,160
(Please donate for temple maintenance.)
(According to your faith.)

108
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:47,440
Can I have some money?

109
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:52,600
-Here.
-Okay.

110
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:56,160
The first box is for water and electricity.

111
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:58,680
Obstacles will flow away,
and life won’t get stuck.

112
00:08:58,680 --> 00:09:00,680
And you’ll only meet light.

113
00:09:01,880 --> 00:09:04,520
The second box is for food donations.

114
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:06,560
You’ll have plenty to eat and use.

115
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,480
and live a prosperous life.

116
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:10,760
Amen. And...

117
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:12,840
What about this one, P’?

118
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,800
"Senasaná."

119
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:16,000
What does that mean?

120
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,280
It means.

121
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:19,160
the buildings inside the temple.

122
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:21,840
Donate to this one, and you’ll get a new home.

123
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,720
and a stable life.

124
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:26,680
And get married and have a family.

125
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:33,240
What?

126
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,600
You don’t want to get married?

127
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,800
I don’t know.

128
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:46,760
May Luk Chang settle down.

129
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,800
and marry Si.

130
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:11,120
Here you go.

131
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:14,680
Put all of this in.

132
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:19,880
Si.

133
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:54,360
Here it comes.

134
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:57,080
Fresh and hot, here you go.

135
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:00,480
So hot.

136
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:03,320
Hot just like the weather now.

137
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:05,520
-Thank you.
-Enjoy eating.

138
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:08,240
Si, careful, it’s hot. Wait.

139
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:20,840
Why are you eating like that?

140
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:22,360
Is it good?

141
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:23,920
I’m used to it.

142
00:11:24,040 --> 00:11:26,560
My mom used to make it like this when I was little.

143
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:28,640
And when I dream about my mom.

144
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:32,160
I wake up early and eat pa tong go like this.

145
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:34,680
So you dreamed about your mom last night.

146
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:35,840
Yeah.

147
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:37,520
What did you dream?

148
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:39,760
I dreamed that...

149
00:11:40,040 --> 00:11:41,520
My mom came to see me.

150
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:43,480
And I told her.

151
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:45,000
Mom.

152
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:47,240
Your daughter has a girlfriend now.

153
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:51,720
You really love imagining things.

154
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:53,880
Who said I’d be your girlfriend?

155
00:11:54,160 --> 00:11:55,240
Or...

156
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:57,720
you don’t want to be a girlfriend, but...

157
00:11:57,880 --> 00:11:59,480
you want to be...

158
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:00,520
a wife.

159
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,120
P’.

160
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:03,880
How can you say that?

161
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:05,520
Crazy.

162
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,240
Want to try eating it like this?

163
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:14,640
That’s good. My hands won’t get messy.

164
00:12:14,680 --> 00:12:15,680
Here.

165
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:19,320
Here.

166
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,560
It’s actually pretty good.

167
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:37,280
P’.

168
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:40,040
Can I ask you something?

169
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:44,800
Do you really like me?

170
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:47,680
After everything I’ve done.

171
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:49,440
you’re still asking.

172
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:51,400
how much I like you?

173
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:55,880
It’s just that I’m...

174
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:57,280
I’m this stubborn.

175
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:59,440
What is there for you to like about me?

176
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:02,520
I’m moody and I snap easily.

177
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:05,360
My personality isn’t good, and I’m harsh too.

178
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:10,960
I think the way you’re harsh.

179
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:13,640
is because you’re trying to protect yourself.

180
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:15,880
Even if it’s a bit the wrong way.

181
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:18,240
I think I understand you.

182
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:24,440
And also.

183
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:27,400
I don’t think you’re as bad as people see you.

184
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:30,400
Life in Bangkok is chaotic.

185
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,720
It’s not peaceful like here.

186
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:36,120
There’s so much competition.

187
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:37,800
Everything is rushed.

188
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:40,240
So you get hot-tempered.

189
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,760
and easily irritated.

190
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:44,760
But when you’re in an environment like this.

191
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:48,720
you slow down.

192
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:51,120
You smile more and laugh more easily.

193
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:53,120
and you feel happier.

194
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:58,960
Maybe you’re right.

195
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:04,320
Hey.

196
00:14:05,760 --> 00:14:07,160
What is this called?

197
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:09,080
Suphan pear.

198
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:11,440
Try dipping it in Ovaltine.

199
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:14,160
Want to try it?

200
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,280
I knew it.

201
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:18,880
Jiw.

202
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:21,120
What is it, P’?

203
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:26,200
Oh, P’ and Parrot lady.

204
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:28,440
Where have you been?

205
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:31,920
You two are always glued together these days.

206
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,280
Wherever you are.

207
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:39,040
Parrot lady is there too.

208
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:40,640
It’s like.

209
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:42,280
wherever Pidpee is.

210
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:44,920
Muedmon has to be there too.

211
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:47,200
Hey.

212
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:48,600
You beef tapeworm.

213
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:50,040
Are you calling me a buffalo?

214
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:52,960
Come on, I was just making a comparison.

215
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,160
P’.

216
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:58,040
I think actually.

217
00:14:58,040 --> 00:15:00,280
the environment here is great.

218
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:01,880
Except for one thing.

219
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,760
your little lackey.

220
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:04,800
What?

221
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:05,920
Just now.

222
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:07,400
what did you call her?

223
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:08,760
P’ Klao?

224
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:10,240
Yeah, why?

225
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:12,720
Then I’m charging you a royalty fee.

226
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:15,520
“P’ Klao” belongs to me alone.

227
00:15:15,680 --> 00:15:18,600
P’ Klao, P’ Klao, P’ Klao.

228
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:19,640
Why?

229
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:22,720
Call it all you want.

230
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:25,400
But I’ll charge you 200.

231
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:28,200
No, make it 500.

232
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:30,400
That word belongs to me alone.

233
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:31,600
No one else can use it.

234
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:33,440
Jiw, Jiw.

235
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:34,960
Is the tractor fixed yet?

236
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:36,480
All done, P’.

237
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:43,600
A vehicle? A tractor?

238
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:46,000
What kind of vehicle is that?

239
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:49,120
Do you want to try riding it?

240
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:51,960
I want to try driving it, P’ Klao.

241
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:53,840
Then when we go back.

242
00:15:53,880 --> 00:15:55,560
you have to teach me how to drive.

243
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:58,640
-Please, please.
-Okay, I’ll teach you myself.

244
00:15:58,680 --> 00:16:00,080
Then before we go back.

245
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:02,600
let’s have some sali cake first.

246
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:05,120
Si.

247
00:16:11,760 --> 00:16:13,240
Are you okay, P’?

248
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:17,720
Where are you going?

249
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:22,360
So freaking cool.

250
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:26,560
I’m always this cool, obviously.

251
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:33,600
I’ll teach you.

252
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,200
Right here, press here.

253
00:16:37,280 --> 00:16:38,840
Then turn this.

254
00:16:38,920 --> 00:16:40,160
Turn it.

255
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:42,040
Turn it, come on.

256
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:43,920
Turn, turn, turn.

257
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:45,120
Give it some tease.

258
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:46,280
Hurry up.

259
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:48,720
-Can you do it?
-How hard could it be?

260
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:51,600
-Can you do it?
-Hold it properly or it’ll spill.

261
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:54,400
-Be careful or it’ll spill.
-Watch it.

262
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:57,760
-Here?
-Yes, and press here.

263
00:16:57,800 --> 00:16:58,800
The white thing.

264
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:00,600
Yep.

265
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:01,680
Yeah.

266
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:05,400
You got this.

267
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:06,839
That’s it, go for it.

268
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:08,800
Si.

269
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:10,119
Are you okay?

270
00:17:10,359 --> 00:17:12,839
My nails are all scratched, P’.

271
00:17:13,319 --> 00:17:16,119
Next time I won’t let you do this again.

272
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:19,440
Look, your pretty nails are all scratched.

273
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:22,599
Check for me if it’s a wound.

274
00:17:24,560 --> 00:17:26,560
"My nails are all scratched."

275
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:37,200
Did a bone get stuck in your throat?

276
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,360
You tapeworm.

277
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:39,960
Just go away.

278
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:41,520
"It hurts so much."

279
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:42,880
You’re gonna get it.

280
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:44,440
"It hurts, it hurts."

281
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:46,600
Jiw, you can go now.

282
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:48,560
Oh, P’.

283
00:17:48,560 --> 00:17:50,240
I was going to head back with you.

284
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:52,280
Oh right, P’.

285
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:55,880
Your sister-in-law is a doctor, right?

286
00:17:56,360 --> 00:17:57,560
Why don’t you go see her?

287
00:17:58,520 --> 00:18:00,520
Wow, I didn’t know.

288
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:02,240
you care about me too.

289
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:04,200
But I’m not that hurt.

290
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,240
It’s not serious enough to see a doctor.

291
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:07,720
Maybe not yet.

292
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:09,080
I wasn’t talking to you.

293
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,320
I was talking to my sister.

294
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:12,680
Something’s wrong with her,
like she got bitten by something.

295
00:18:12,720 --> 00:18:14,600
You’re starting to act weird like her.

296
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:17,120
-She’s definitely been cursed.
-Jiw.

297
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:19,960
-Stop it.
-Are you saying I cursed your sister?

298
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:23,000
Stop bothering her.

299
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:25,200
And I’m not sick either.

300
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:27,400
I’m just...

301
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:29,240
In love.

302
00:18:29,560 --> 00:18:32,200
-In love.
-How could you say that in front of him?

303
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:33,440
In love?

304
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:35,600
-I still feel pain.
-In love.

305
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,000
Hey.

306
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:42,040
I’m heading back.
I can’t stay here anymore.

307
00:18:42,560 --> 00:18:43,760
I’m gonna throw up.

308
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:47,760
Let’s go.

309
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:51,440
If these two break up,
I’ll never believe in love again.

310
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:53,000
You’re so dramatic.

311
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:00,080
Drive safely.

312
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:06,560
Hey, P’.

313
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:07,960
Next time.

314
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:10,440
you should rein in your lackey.

315
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:14,240
He’s getting more and more annoying.

316
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:17,000
Don’t take it to heart.

317
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:19,320
Actually, he’s not doing so well right now.

318
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:22,880
He went to see a doctor
and is just getting by each day.

319
00:19:22,960 --> 00:19:25,240
Not sure how long he can keep going.

320
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:27,080
Really?

321
00:19:27,080 --> 00:19:30,040
At first glance, he doesn’t look sick at all.

322
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:31,520
He’s pretty strong.

323
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,480
I feel bad for him.

324
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:36,200
This morning when we went to pray.

325
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:38,320
I made a wish for Jiw too.

326
00:19:38,360 --> 00:19:41,880
I asked for him to be healthy
and recover soon.

327
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:45,600
If he knew someone cared
about him this much.

328
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:47,360
he’d definitely be happy.

329
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:53,040
Come on, let’s go. Go sit and wait.

330
00:19:55,560 --> 00:19:56,720
Go on. You’re amazing.

331
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:19,760
Where is it?

332
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:22,480
Si.

333
00:20:22,520 --> 00:20:23,640
What are you looking for?

334
00:20:24,040 --> 00:20:25,600
My bracelet.

335
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:27,840
I remember putting it in my bag.

336
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:29,360
But I don’t know where it went.

337
00:20:30,120 --> 00:20:32,480
A bracelet? Come on, I’ll help you look.

338
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:36,400
Is it in here?

339
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:46,080
Where did it go?

340
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:47,480
Or.

341
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:49,360
did you drop it at home?

342
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:51,440
No way, P’.

343
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:53,360
I remember.

344
00:20:53,360 --> 00:20:55,160
I put it in my bag.

345
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:57,320
This is so annoying.

346
00:20:57,360 --> 00:20:59,760
It’s my favorite bracelet too.

347
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,560
It’s already lost.

348
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:04,360
Getting upset about it.

349
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:06,080
won’t bring it back.

350
00:21:06,120 --> 00:21:07,160
And it’ll.

351
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:09,560
give you wrinkles and make you age faster.

352
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:12,120
That’s true.

353
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:13,400
Let me see.

354
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:21,440
Calm down.

355
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:35,680
So...

356
00:21:36,360 --> 00:21:37,440
Where are you going?

357
00:21:37,680 --> 00:21:38,880
Back to the field again?

358
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:41,160
Yeah. Want to come with me?

359
00:21:42,600 --> 00:21:44,200
I’ll just sleep.

360
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:46,080
and wait for you at home.

361
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:47,720
I lost my stuff.

362
00:21:47,840 --> 00:21:50,640
so I’m annoyed.
I’m not in the mood for anything, P’.

363
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:54,440
Okay. I’ll hurry back.

364
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:55,480
Hm?

365
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:01,680
I’m going.

366
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:39,480
Want to buy some food? Food.

367
00:22:39,840 --> 00:22:42,200
It’s so quiet today.

368
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:44,880
Where did everyone go?

369
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:48,640
Hey.

370
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:50,280
Wait here, darling.

371
00:22:50,320 --> 00:22:51,360
Hey.

372
00:22:53,360 --> 00:22:54,760
Come here.

373
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:55,840
Let me see.

374
00:22:55,840 --> 00:22:59,480
-What do you have today?
-Oh my, wishing you luck and riches.

375
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:01,480
Take a look, miss. Go ahead.

376
00:23:05,480 --> 00:23:06,600
What is it?

377
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,320
Why so shocked, girl?

378
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:10,680
Never seen a beauty before?

379
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:13,680
What kind of makeup is that?
You scared me.

380
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:17,120
That shocked? Or have you
never seen a beauty before?

381
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:19,560
I just did my makeup like usual.

382
00:23:19,840 --> 00:23:21,240
What can I do?

383
00:23:21,320 --> 00:23:23,480
My stuff just isn’t selling.

384
00:23:23,560 --> 00:23:25,480
No matter where I park,
no one buys anything.

385
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:27,440
It’s dead quiet.
I don’t know where everyone went.

386
00:23:27,480 --> 00:23:29,360
So I did my makeup out of spite.

387
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:31,960
Hmm, so do you know
why you have no customers?

388
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:36,160
You’ve got a pretty face,
and you look like you love snacks.

389
00:23:36,280 --> 00:23:38,320
I’ve got something good
I just got from Bangkok.

390
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:41,040
"Bear’s Choice Cornflakes."

391
00:23:41,680 --> 00:23:44,280
If you buy this from their IG,
it’s super expensive.

392
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:45,760
Here, buy it from me.

393
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:46,960
-Hmm.
-Wanna try it?

394
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,240
Hook me up, sis.

395
00:23:48,320 --> 00:23:50,160
I’ll check out your snacks for you.

396
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:52,960
Why do you have so much leftover, sis?

397
00:23:53,040 --> 00:23:54,560
Do you restock daily?

398
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:55,600
Oh please.

399
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:57,440
I can’t restock every day, kid.

400
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:58,800
Gas eats up all the profit.

401
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:00,400
I restock every 2–3 days.

402
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:03,280
That’s right. Yeah.

403
00:24:04,320 --> 00:24:05,720
-Sis.
-What.

404
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:08,640
Do you play "Tok Tok"?

405
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:11,600
-Tok Tok?
-Tok Tok, you know, Tok Tok.

406
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:13,040
Social media.

407
00:24:13,880 --> 00:24:16,080
-Filming Tok Tok clips.
-Yeah, exactly.

408
00:24:17,040 --> 00:24:19,160
I love watching it. I watch it every day.

409
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,400
"It's so hot out."

410
00:24:20,440 --> 00:24:23,280
"I'm human, not a robot
that can stand in the sun all day."

411
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:24,640
"If you want to buy,"

412
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:27,320
-"then go buy a robot,"
-"to use in the kitchen."

413
00:24:28,120 --> 00:24:29,520
Alright, enough.
Sis, let’s get to the point.

414
00:24:29,680 --> 00:24:31,480
Wow, you watch even more than me.

415
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:32,840
So...

416
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:35,480
You watch a lot, but have you ever posted?

417
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:37,240
"Pose"? I strike poses every day.

418
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:38,440
No.

419
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:40,440
I mean posting videos of yourself.

420
00:24:40,440 --> 00:24:42,560
Like making content and stuff.

421
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:45,240
I don’t know how to do that.

422
00:24:45,280 --> 00:24:46,800
I only know how to watch.

423
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:51,280
Who are you looking at?
Is something there?

424
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:53,680
Hey, you’re looking again.

425
00:24:55,320 --> 00:24:57,560
-Today I probably won’t sell anything.
-I’ve got an idea, sis.

426
00:24:58,840 --> 00:25:01,800
Attention everyone in the 918 community.

427
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:04,840
Lady and Gentleman,
My name is Jae Pumpuang.

428
00:25:04,880 --> 00:25:06,920
If you want good and fresh stuff,
it’s all right here on this truck.

429
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:10,240
-Let’s start with the first set of products.
-They’re working way above their pay.

430
00:25:14,120 --> 00:25:17,080
So you helped them with makeup and

431
00:25:17,120 --> 00:25:18,240
taught them how to livestream?

432
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:19,800
Mm, yeah.

433
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:23,480
These days, just selling isn’t enough, sis.

434
00:25:23,520 --> 00:25:26,080
You’ve got to use marketing strategies too.

435
00:25:26,440 --> 00:25:28,360
I told them

436
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,560
to post every day.

437
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:31,920
And keep updating what’s new.

438
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:33,240
So people know.

439
00:25:34,120 --> 00:25:36,640
Thank you for helping them.

440
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:38,160
They’re pitiful.

441
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:40,120
They just got dumped
by a younger boyfriend.

442
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:42,200
That explains it.

443
00:25:42,760 --> 00:25:44,200
Why lately they’ve been

444
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:46,000
doing everything alone all day.

445
00:25:46,040 --> 00:25:49,240
Driving, hauling stuff, and selling.

446
00:25:52,120 --> 00:25:53,480
I was thinking,

447
00:25:53,560 --> 00:25:56,080
should I go home and bring unused makeup

448
00:25:56,120 --> 00:25:57,360
to give them?

449
00:25:57,720 --> 00:26:00,000
Do you think they’d mind me?

450
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:02,960
Who would mind?

451
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:04,080
Your stuff

452
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:06,000
is all good and expensive.

453
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,000
And what did you buy so much of?

454
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,840
It’s Lao seafood, sis.

455
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:17,080
Tonight, I’m thinking of cooking for you.

456
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:18,800
You cook?

457
00:26:18,880 --> 00:26:19,880
Mm.

458
00:26:20,040 --> 00:26:21,080
Why?

459
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:25,520
Don’t underestimate me.

460
00:26:25,520 --> 00:26:29,000
I’m way better than you think, just saying.

461
00:26:30,800 --> 00:26:32,000
Go ahead.

462
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:33,560
Be my guest.

463
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:37,640
Just don’t burn my house down.

464
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:40,560
Just wait and see.

465
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:16,720
Do you actually know how to cook?

466
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:19,800
Just wait and see.

467
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:28,680
Here.

468
00:27:34,120 --> 00:27:36,040
What are you doing?

469
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:42,280
I’ll be your assistant today.

470
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:43,640
Good.

471
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:45,080
Don’t be slow.

472
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:47,280
Here you go, one flower.

473
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:48,720
It stinks.

474
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:51,160
Second flower.

475
00:27:53,640 --> 00:27:55,080
Last one.

476
00:27:55,120 --> 00:27:56,680
Mini-Heart.

477
00:27:57,480 --> 00:27:59,000
I can do it too.

478
00:28:06,880 --> 00:28:08,360
Get back to cooking.

479
00:28:08,920 --> 00:28:10,520
Or we won’t get to eat.

480
00:28:17,720 --> 00:28:18,840
Excuse me for a second.

481
00:28:22,320 --> 00:28:23,520
Hello, Khun Song.

482
00:28:23,560 --> 00:28:25,200
Hello, Khun Klao.

483
00:28:25,240 --> 00:28:27,920
I’m calling about the contract amendment.

484
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:30,200
The rent reduction
for the land you helped adjust.

485
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:31,280
In exchange for

486
00:28:31,320 --> 00:28:33,560
the Suphan Hom Mali Rice 918 project.

487
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:37,000
Are you available to meet in Bangkok?

488
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:39,560
It’ll probably be in a couple of days.

489
00:28:39,560 --> 00:28:40,960
Before I can go there.

490
00:28:40,960 --> 00:28:43,200
I’ll call you once I have a confirmed date.

491
00:28:43,400 --> 00:28:44,440
And...

492
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:47,280
Is my sister with you?

493
00:28:47,720 --> 00:28:48,800
She’s here.

494
00:28:52,520 --> 00:28:54,520
She’s cooking dinner.

495
00:28:54,520 --> 00:28:55,560
What?

496
00:28:55,920 --> 00:28:58,080
Sis Si? Cooking dinner?

497
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:01,280
I’ve never seen her do housework in my life.

498
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:05,160
Why did she turn into
a completely different person in Suphan?

499
00:29:05,760 --> 00:29:08,440
I really want to see it with my own eyes.

500
00:29:08,520 --> 00:29:10,720
Come visit here sometime.

501
00:29:10,760 --> 00:29:12,400
And bring your parents too.

502
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:14,880
Maybe you’ll get to see something surprising.

503
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:18,000
I’ll bring my parents along then.

504
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:19,920
They’d definitely want to go.

505
00:29:20,320 --> 00:29:21,360
Alright.

506
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:23,280
Wait, Klao.

507
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:25,960
Well...

508
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:30,280
I actually have something I want to ask.

509
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:32,160
What is it?

510
00:29:33,920 --> 00:29:37,280
What are you and my sister now?

511
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:41,520
Well...

512
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:48,920
It’s okay.

513
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,720
Not answering...

514
00:29:50,760 --> 00:29:52,240
is an answer too.

515
00:29:57,840 --> 00:29:58,880
By the way...

516
00:29:59,040 --> 00:30:01,520
why are you rooting for me and her?

517
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:03,680
You don’t dislike your own sister

518
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:05,000
so much that...

519
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:07,040
you’re trying to send her far away, right?

520
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:09,280
It’s not like that at all.

521
00:30:09,360 --> 00:30:10,360
It’s just...

522
00:30:10,400 --> 00:30:11,480
I feel like...

523
00:30:11,760 --> 00:30:14,680
she’s been happier since she met you.

524
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:16,480
And...

525
00:30:16,520 --> 00:30:19,760
no one has ever talked to her
for more than three sentences

526
00:30:19,800 --> 00:30:21,120
without getting annoyed.

527
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:23,000
Except you.

528
00:30:23,240 --> 00:30:24,240
Oh.

529
00:30:26,640 --> 00:30:27,640
Okay.

530
00:30:28,560 --> 00:30:30,040
See you then.

531
00:30:39,080 --> 00:30:40,120
No.

532
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:41,760
I didn’t even ask anything yet.

533
00:30:42,240 --> 00:30:43,240
Oh really?

534
00:30:45,960 --> 00:30:46,960
Here.

535
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:48,000
Hot, right?

536
00:30:51,080 --> 00:30:52,080
Wow.

537
00:30:52,080 --> 00:30:53,880
Ta-da.

538
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:56,840
Si Restaurant is now open.

539
00:30:59,560 --> 00:31:00,720
Here.

540
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:02,240
First dish.

541
00:31:02,720 --> 00:31:04,640
Stir-fried seafood with chili paste and basil.

542
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:06,920
And this is stir-fried glass noodles
with water mimosa and shrimp.

543
00:31:06,960 --> 00:31:08,200
And...

544
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:10,440
I fried some eggs too.

545
00:31:11,400 --> 00:31:13,720
Everything looks so tasty, Si.

546
00:31:13,760 --> 00:31:15,720
You can really cook like this?

547
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:19,280
I followed cooking clips while doing it, sis.

548
00:31:19,320 --> 00:31:20,640
This is actually my first time

549
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:22,960
doing it myself.

550
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:24,640
You’re really

551
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:26,920
both skilled and talented.

552
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:28,320
Amazing.

553
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:31,280
You’re overpraising me.

554
00:31:31,320 --> 00:31:33,760
I don’t know if it’ll taste good or not.

555
00:31:35,360 --> 00:31:36,840
Come on, let’s eat.

556
00:31:39,040 --> 00:31:40,840
Si, wait a second.

557
00:31:41,520 --> 00:31:42,600
I’ll be right back.

558
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:43,720
Where are you going, sis?

559
00:31:46,320 --> 00:31:48,400
Here it is.

560
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:51,640
My precious has arrived.

561
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:52,960
What is that?

562
00:31:54,080 --> 00:31:55,160
Plum wine.

563
00:31:55,160 --> 00:31:56,280
This jar.

564
00:31:56,440 --> 00:31:57,560
I made it myself.

565
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:02,520
You’re not over what happened last time
you got drunk yet?

566
00:32:02,920 --> 00:32:04,560
If you get drunk again tonight,

567
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:05,920
I’m not taking responsibility.

568
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:07,400
Whoa, Si.

569
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:09,360
Delicious food

570
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:11,080
has to be paired with

571
00:32:11,120 --> 00:32:13,200
a refreshing drink.

572
00:32:13,280 --> 00:32:15,160
Just a little bit.

573
00:32:15,680 --> 00:32:16,760
I promise

574
00:32:16,800 --> 00:32:18,120
I won’t get drunk.

575
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:20,320
You can only drink this much.

576
00:32:23,080 --> 00:32:24,120
I’ll take this much.

577
00:32:25,760 --> 00:32:26,760
Right here.

578
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:28,280
Please, right here.

579
00:32:31,520 --> 00:32:33,160
Right? Just this once.

580
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:34,640
Come on, let’s eat.

581
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:41,440
I’ll serve you some shrimp first.

582
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:43,800
Here.

583
00:32:43,840 --> 00:32:45,200
That’s your third bowl.

584
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:46,480
Sis.

585
00:32:47,080 --> 00:32:49,280
You’ve already had three plates of rice.

586
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:51,360
Aren’t you full?

587
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:52,440
I think

588
00:32:52,440 --> 00:32:54,240
you won’t throw up from the plum wine.

589
00:32:54,280 --> 00:32:56,920
You’ll probably throw up
from overeating instead.

590
00:32:57,560 --> 00:33:01,240
Well, who told you to cook this delicious?

591
00:33:02,480 --> 00:33:04,080
Now I’m in trouble.

592
00:33:04,120 --> 00:33:05,440
I just want to keep eating.

593
00:33:05,440 --> 00:33:06,560
I don’t want to be full.

594
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:09,440
Sis.

595
00:33:09,920 --> 00:33:11,560
Can I ask you honestly?

596
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:13,440
Is it really that good?

597
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:14,920
Or...

598
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:17,880
are you just saying that to please me?

599
00:33:18,680 --> 00:33:20,960
Why would I lie to you?

600
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:22,600
Hmm.

601
00:33:22,760 --> 00:33:24,400
Well, that’s true.

602
00:33:24,880 --> 00:33:26,840
You’re a straightforward person, but...

603
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:28,840
every time you speak...

604
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:31,520
You never make the listener lose confidence.

605
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:33,160
That’s it, right?

606
00:33:33,160 --> 00:33:34,760
The good side of Klao.

607
00:33:35,640 --> 00:33:37,200
My good side?

608
00:33:37,240 --> 00:33:38,640
Is that all?

609
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:41,320
That’s already a lot.

610
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:47,200
Well, at least I have a good side in your eyes.

611
00:33:48,520 --> 00:33:51,080
Take a big bite. Here.

612
00:33:58,720 --> 00:34:00,120
Wait, wait.

613
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:01,640
Let’s have a toast.

614
00:34:02,280 --> 00:34:03,280
Cheers.

615
00:34:13,360 --> 00:34:14,480
Si.

616
00:34:14,520 --> 00:34:16,120
Can’t you stay a bit longer?

617
00:34:16,159 --> 00:34:17,800
Why do you have to go home?

618
00:34:19,280 --> 00:34:20,960
I think I’m going to...

619
00:34:21,120 --> 00:34:24,120
start my own business seriously.

620
00:34:24,199 --> 00:34:26,480
So I want to go back and look for a way.

621
00:34:26,880 --> 00:34:27,920
And...

622
00:34:27,960 --> 00:34:30,199
you don’t want to be a CEO anymore?

623
00:34:31,480 --> 00:34:32,600
Well...

624
00:34:32,679 --> 00:34:34,960
since I’m not the favorite child,

625
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:38,239
I have to find my own way to grow.

626
00:34:40,239 --> 00:34:41,960
Don’t think like that.

627
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:45,320
No parent doesn’t love their child.

628
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:52,920
Si.

629
00:34:53,199 --> 00:34:54,800
Let me ask you something.

630
00:34:56,320 --> 00:34:57,360
So...

631
00:34:57,400 --> 00:34:58,880
all this time,

632
00:34:59,120 --> 00:35:01,640
have you gone to work at the company at all?

633
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:05,240
No.

634
00:35:06,560 --> 00:35:07,720
And...

635
00:35:08,240 --> 00:35:11,400
do you still have money to spend freely?

636
00:35:13,160 --> 00:35:15,040
Yeah, I do.

637
00:35:16,200 --> 00:35:17,280
And...

638
00:35:17,280 --> 00:35:20,280
do you have to wake up early
to work like your sister?

639
00:35:25,920 --> 00:35:26,960
And...

640
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:29,360
have your parents ever scolded you?

641
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:31,080
Not counting the times

642
00:35:31,080 --> 00:35:33,200
you acted out at them first.

643
00:35:36,120 --> 00:35:37,200
Well...

644
00:35:37,560 --> 00:35:39,560
they complain sometimes, but...

645
00:35:39,720 --> 00:35:41,840
I don’t see them really scolding me.

646
00:35:43,240 --> 00:35:44,400
See?

647
00:35:44,680 --> 00:35:46,680
You get to live comfortably

648
00:35:46,680 --> 00:35:48,600
without having to work,

649
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:50,680
and you get everything you want.

650
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:54,120
So who exactly is the favorite child?

651
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:57,040
Your sister,

652
00:35:57,080 --> 00:35:59,120
who has to work so hard

653
00:35:59,440 --> 00:36:01,160
to get what she wants?

654
00:36:01,360 --> 00:36:03,280
versus you, who does nothing,

655
00:36:04,080 --> 00:36:06,520
and your parents just hand you everything.

656
00:36:07,680 --> 00:36:08,840
I think...

657
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:12,320
you’re misunderstanding
your parents and your sister.

658
00:36:16,560 --> 00:36:18,520
Sis, saying that,

659
00:36:18,600 --> 00:36:21,400
do you want me to go back
and work with my family?

660
00:36:23,240 --> 00:36:24,880
That’s not what I mean.

661
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:28,440
I do agree

662
00:36:28,440 --> 00:36:30,840
if you want to grow on your own.

663
00:36:31,560 --> 00:36:32,560
But...

664
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:35,760
I don’t want you to see your family
in a negative way

665
00:36:35,880 --> 00:36:37,440
when in reality,

666
00:36:37,720 --> 00:36:39,480
everyone loves you so much.

667
00:36:44,200 --> 00:36:45,240
That...

668
00:36:46,120 --> 00:36:48,400
what you said makes sense.

669
00:36:49,160 --> 00:36:51,440
It might really be true.

670
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:54,200
And...

671
00:36:54,200 --> 00:36:55,840
what do you want to do?

672
00:36:58,400 --> 00:37:00,680
I want to work in real estate.

673
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:01,960
You know,

674
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:05,560
I even have house designs I really like.

675
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:09,240
That’s nice.

676
00:37:09,280 --> 00:37:11,960
That you know what you want to do

677
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:13,720
and what you like.

678
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:18,520
But...

679
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:21,480
Real estate is hard though, sis.

680
00:37:21,560 --> 00:37:22,840
I’m scared.

681
00:37:22,880 --> 00:37:25,520
Scared that I’ll fail.

682
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:27,520
You know,

683
00:37:27,640 --> 00:37:30,280
if I mess it up,

684
00:37:30,400 --> 00:37:32,440
it won’t just be embarrassing.

685
00:37:33,600 --> 00:37:35,720
I might lose everything.

686
00:37:39,320 --> 00:37:40,560
Then how about this?

687
00:37:41,080 --> 00:37:42,640
You don’t have to be scared.

688
00:37:42,880 --> 00:37:45,800
If you lose everything doing what you love,

689
00:37:46,200 --> 00:37:49,520
I’ll sell all the land under my name.

690
00:37:49,920 --> 00:37:52,040
And give you all the money.

691
00:37:53,760 --> 00:37:55,000
Really, sis?

692
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:56,560
You said it.

693
00:37:57,800 --> 00:38:00,920
But you have to marry me first.

694
00:38:01,200 --> 00:38:02,760
Then I’ll do it.

695
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:13,160
Look over there.

696
00:38:14,520 --> 00:38:15,520
This?

697
00:38:16,480 --> 00:38:17,520
That one.

698
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:19,280
See it yet?

699
00:38:50,280 --> 00:38:51,440
Hello, P'.

700
00:38:51,880 --> 00:38:53,160
You're not asleep yet?

701
00:38:53,640 --> 00:38:55,040
I'm working.

702
00:38:55,280 --> 00:38:56,520
It's so late.

703
00:38:56,560 --> 00:38:58,320
You're still working?

704
00:38:58,320 --> 00:38:59,360
Yeah.

705
00:38:59,360 --> 00:39:00,680
I got carried away with work.

706
00:39:00,680 --> 00:39:02,640
I didn’t even notice the time.

707
00:39:02,880 --> 00:39:03,920
And...

708
00:39:04,040 --> 00:39:05,960
What are you doing?
Why aren't you sleeping?

709
00:39:06,080 --> 00:39:08,240
I was thinking about you.

710
00:39:08,960 --> 00:39:11,000
Pao misses you too.

711
00:39:13,120 --> 00:39:15,680
Pao, why aren't you asleep yet, baby?

712
00:39:18,240 --> 00:39:20,120
Hey, what are you doing to Pao?

713
00:39:20,160 --> 00:39:21,600
Why is she crying like that?

714
00:39:25,080 --> 00:39:27,520
I moved her to sleep in another room today.

715
00:39:27,560 --> 00:39:30,400
Why did you make her sleep in another room?

716
00:39:31,120 --> 00:39:32,200
Well...

717
00:39:32,240 --> 00:39:34,320
I was thinking...

718
00:39:34,520 --> 00:39:36,800
that you were right here

719
00:39:37,200 --> 00:39:38,440
in front of me.

720
00:39:38,760 --> 00:39:39,760
Right now.

721
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:43,360
So I didn’t want Pao to see.

722
00:39:44,640 --> 00:39:45,640
P'.

723
00:39:45,920 --> 00:39:47,360
Let me tell you,

724
00:39:48,120 --> 00:39:50,080
I’m about to...

725
00:39:50,320 --> 00:39:51,400
Yeah.

726
00:39:52,480 --> 00:39:53,720
And you...

727
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:55,520
just imagine

728
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:58,080
that I’m right there too.

729
00:42:25,880 --> 00:42:27,360
If it weren’t for the fact

730
00:42:27,760 --> 00:42:29,680
that I don’t drive at night,

731
00:42:30,280 --> 00:42:32,920
I’d drive to you right now.

732
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:34,360
You know?

733
00:42:35,080 --> 00:42:36,600
Then tomorrow,

734
00:42:36,800 --> 00:42:39,000
hurry and come see me.

735
00:42:39,560 --> 00:42:40,560
Okay.

736
00:42:40,920 --> 00:42:42,960
I’ll rush to you first thing in the morning.

737
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:46,720
We have an 8 a.m. meeting today.

738
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:48,480
I think we should hurry or we’ll hit traffic.

739
00:42:48,520 --> 00:42:50,560
We can just grab breakfast at the office.

740
00:42:50,600 --> 00:42:51,600
Right?

741
00:42:51,680 --> 00:42:53,080
Oh, Klao.

742
00:42:53,120 --> 00:42:54,480
You’re here so early.

743
00:42:54,720 --> 00:42:56,120
Is something important?

744
00:42:58,720 --> 00:43:00,760
Is it about the contract signing?

745
00:43:00,800 --> 00:43:02,640
I forgot to tell you,

746
00:43:02,680 --> 00:43:04,320
you have to sign it at the office.

747
00:43:04,360 --> 00:43:05,560
No.

748
00:43:05,600 --> 00:43:07,200
About the contract,

749
00:43:07,200 --> 00:43:09,880
I was planning to discuss it
at the office this afternoon.

750
00:43:10,240 --> 00:43:12,360
But right now...

751
00:43:12,560 --> 00:43:14,320
I want to see Si.

752
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:17,080
-Oh.
-Oh, she’s still asleep.

753
00:43:17,680 --> 00:43:19,040
Is it something urgent?

754
00:43:19,520 --> 00:43:20,680
Well...

755
00:43:21,240 --> 00:43:22,680
it is urgent.

756
00:43:24,520 --> 00:43:27,920
Hey, did Si cause trouble again?

757
00:43:28,640 --> 00:43:30,960
It’s nothing serious.

758
00:43:32,080 --> 00:43:34,200
But... it’s urgent.

759
00:43:34,720 --> 00:43:37,000
If it’s not a big deal,

760
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:39,480
why come to our house this early?

761
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:42,320
Um...

762
00:43:42,360 --> 00:43:44,640
I think I’ll just go wake her up myself.

763
00:43:44,960 --> 00:43:48,280
As long as she didn’t cause any trouble,
that’s already good, right?

764
00:43:48,320 --> 00:43:50,200
You can wait inside first.

765
00:43:50,280 --> 00:43:53,240
I’ll have the maid call her for you, okay?

766
00:43:53,520 --> 00:43:54,680
Or...

767
00:43:54,720 --> 00:43:57,080
you can go to her room yourself.

768
00:43:57,240 --> 00:43:58,280
Oh.

769
00:43:58,920 --> 00:44:00,600
I can do that?

770
00:44:00,680 --> 00:44:02,160
-Of course.
-Of course.

771
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:04,400
Very good.

772
00:44:05,880 --> 00:44:08,880
We heard Si stayed over
at your place several nights.

773
00:44:09,520 --> 00:44:11,680
She must trust you quite a lot.

774
00:44:11,720 --> 00:44:12,880
As for us,

775
00:44:12,880 --> 00:44:14,120
we don’t think you

776
00:44:14,120 --> 00:44:16,600
-would do anything bad to our daughter.
-Right.

777
00:44:17,320 --> 00:44:18,720
Okay, make yourself at home.

778
00:44:18,920 --> 00:44:19,920
Okay.

779
00:44:20,720 --> 00:44:21,760
Bye.

780
00:44:24,960 --> 00:44:27,200
I’ll have the maid take you there.

781
00:44:27,200 --> 00:44:29,680
We have a meeting to attend.

782
00:44:33,240 --> 00:44:34,680
This way, please.

783
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:47,400
Si.

784
00:44:49,720 --> 00:44:50,720
Si.

785
00:44:57,160 --> 00:44:58,360
What?

786
00:44:58,520 --> 00:44:59,800
P'?

787
00:45:00,320 --> 00:45:03,000
What are you doing here so early?
It’s not even 7 yet.

788
00:45:03,040 --> 00:45:06,040
You told me to come see you early.

789
00:45:06,080 --> 00:45:07,080
But...

790
00:45:09,200 --> 00:45:11,400
I haven’t brushed my teeth yet.

791
00:45:14,880 --> 00:45:17,520
Are you done yet, P'?
It’s taking so long.

792
00:45:17,760 --> 00:45:19,440
I’m done, but...

793
00:45:19,440 --> 00:45:21,160
I’m not used to it.

794
00:45:21,200 --> 00:45:22,640
Can I change it back?

795
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:24,400
No.

796
00:45:25,000 --> 00:45:26,960
Come out and let me see. Hurry.

797
00:45:27,520 --> 00:45:28,880
I’m shy.

798
00:45:29,760 --> 00:45:31,480
If you don’t come out,

799
00:45:31,480 --> 00:45:33,120
I’m breaking the door in.

800
00:45:33,560 --> 00:45:36,440
One, two, three.

801
00:45:44,320 --> 00:45:45,720
It looks awful, right?

802
00:45:45,760 --> 00:45:48,200
-Then I’ll go change back.
-Wait, wait, wait.

803
00:45:48,480 --> 00:45:51,120
Who said it looks bad?

804
00:45:59,560 --> 00:46:02,680
It looks absolutely stunning, P'.

805
00:46:04,200 --> 00:46:06,000
You should’ve dressed like this ages ago.

806
00:46:06,160 --> 00:46:08,440
Why were you always in those farm clothes?

807
00:46:08,440 --> 00:46:09,560
Hey.

808
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:12,200
You expect me to wear this to the fields?

809
00:46:12,240 --> 00:46:14,600
Pidpee and Muedmon
would chase me for sure.

810
00:46:14,680 --> 00:46:17,320
Or Jon would come peck me nonstop.

811
00:46:18,320 --> 00:46:19,520
But...

812
00:46:19,640 --> 00:46:21,880
there are still two more outfits.

813
00:46:21,920 --> 00:46:22,960
That’s enough.

814
00:46:23,000 --> 00:46:24,360
One is enough.

815
00:46:25,280 --> 00:46:26,800
P' Klao,

816
00:46:26,840 --> 00:46:29,320
let me see, please.

817
00:46:29,320 --> 00:46:31,200
I want to.

818
00:46:32,480 --> 00:46:35,360
If you weren’t being this cute about it,

819
00:46:35,360 --> 00:46:36,920
I wouldn’t agree.

820
00:46:37,880 --> 00:46:39,360
You’re the cutest. Go on.

821
00:46:40,920 --> 00:46:42,560
Then I’ll leave my phone with you.

822
00:46:42,600 --> 00:46:44,280
-Of course.
-There’s nowhere to put it inside.

823
00:47:07,120 --> 00:47:08,840
We meet again.

824
00:47:09,360 --> 00:47:12,400
Guess we really are meant to be.

825
00:47:12,520 --> 00:47:14,320
No matter where we run, we still meet.

826
00:47:15,400 --> 00:47:16,760
Let’s talk outside.

827
00:47:17,040 --> 00:47:18,040
Why?

828
00:47:18,880 --> 00:47:20,720
Talking here is private enough.

829
00:47:20,880 --> 00:47:21,920
Afraid someone will see?

830
00:47:21,920 --> 00:47:23,320
Or afraid someone will hear?

831
00:47:24,480 --> 00:47:26,000
Are you going to walk out nicely,

832
00:47:26,400 --> 00:47:29,240
or should I call security to drag you out?

833
00:47:29,360 --> 00:47:30,440
Did you forget?

834
00:47:30,440 --> 00:47:32,040
This is my mall.

835
00:47:49,560 --> 00:47:50,760
Say what you want.

836
00:47:52,960 --> 00:47:54,000
Why?

837
00:47:55,440 --> 00:47:57,960
Do couples need a reason to meet?

838
00:47:58,640 --> 00:48:00,200
How many times do I have to say it?

839
00:48:00,280 --> 00:48:01,480
We broke up.

840
00:48:02,200 --> 00:48:04,000
If you want to break up, do it alone.

841
00:48:05,680 --> 00:48:06,880
I’m not breaking up.

842
00:48:08,440 --> 00:48:09,880
I love only you.

843
00:48:10,520 --> 00:48:11,960
Stop lying.

844
00:48:13,680 --> 00:48:16,000
You think I wouldn’t know?

845
00:48:16,680 --> 00:48:19,560
You scammed a foreigner until he
lost everything, and he caught you, right?

846
00:48:19,640 --> 00:48:21,000
That’s why you crawled back.

847
00:48:22,840 --> 00:48:24,600
Jane, Jane.

848
00:48:25,640 --> 00:48:26,680
Let go of me.

849
00:48:26,720 --> 00:48:28,720
-No.
-Jane, what are you doing?

850
00:48:29,080 --> 00:48:30,800
Doing what we used to do together.

851
00:48:31,200 --> 00:48:33,040
Are you going to come nicely,
or do I have to force you?

852
00:48:33,840 --> 00:48:34,960
Let go of me, Jane.

853
00:48:35,280 --> 00:48:36,960
That’s enough, Jane. Let me go.

854
00:48:40,760 --> 00:48:42,640
Do you really have to go this far?

855
00:48:43,800 --> 00:48:44,880
Jane.

856
00:48:44,920 --> 00:48:46,880
Security, security.

857
00:48:46,920 --> 00:48:48,280
What’s going on, Si?

858
00:48:48,280 --> 00:48:50,120
-Get this woman out of here, now.
-Yes, ma’am.

859
00:48:50,200 --> 00:48:51,280
Don’t.

860
00:48:51,960 --> 00:48:53,600
Don’t touch me.

861
00:49:01,120 --> 00:49:02,840
You really want people to see, huh?

862
00:49:08,880 --> 00:49:11,200
We filmed dozens of these clips together.

863
00:49:11,520 --> 00:49:12,680
Don’t you remember?

864
00:49:13,840 --> 00:49:16,000
If these leak all over the internet,

865
00:49:16,560 --> 00:49:18,440
what do you think the media will say?

866
00:49:21,040 --> 00:49:23,120
"Scandalous leaked
clip of a mall heiress."

867
00:49:23,160 --> 00:49:24,880
-You want that?
-Give it to me, Jane.

868
00:49:25,040 --> 00:49:26,480
-Hold her.
-Yes.

869
00:49:28,040 --> 00:49:29,240
-Let go of me.
-Take her out.

870
00:49:29,440 --> 00:49:30,480
Get out.

871
00:49:30,480 --> 00:49:31,480
Let go of me.

872
00:49:31,600 --> 00:49:33,040
-Let go of me.
-Wait.

873
00:49:34,560 --> 00:49:35,560
Jane.

874
00:49:36,640 --> 00:49:38,640
That’s mine. Give it back or
I’ll call the police.

875
00:49:38,640 --> 00:49:40,320
Go ahead. Do it.

876
00:49:40,640 --> 00:49:42,240
I’ll report you right back.

877
00:49:42,440 --> 00:49:43,840
For stealing my bracelet

878
00:49:43,880 --> 00:49:45,000
and my money.

879
00:49:45,160 --> 00:49:46,160
What bracelet?

880
00:49:46,960 --> 00:49:49,000
-I don’t know anything.
-Stop lying.

881
00:49:49,040 --> 00:49:50,440
I said stop lying.

882
00:49:50,960 --> 00:49:52,360
There are CCTV cameras.

883
00:49:52,640 --> 00:49:54,280
Just have the staff check them.

884
00:49:54,520 --> 00:49:55,760
And it’ll be crystal clear

885
00:49:55,800 --> 00:49:57,280
that you’re the one who took it.

886
00:49:58,160 --> 00:50:00,240
Tell all security and every entrance

887
00:50:00,240 --> 00:50:01,400
not to let this woman in again.

888
00:50:01,520 --> 00:50:03,080
-Yes.
-Get her out.

889
00:50:03,080 --> 00:50:05,960
Idiot, you think I only kept
the clips on my phone?

890
00:50:06,760 --> 00:50:08,440
I backed up everything.

891
00:50:08,480 --> 00:50:09,920
You dare treat me like this,

892
00:50:09,920 --> 00:50:12,160
I’ll expose everything about
you to the whole world.

893
00:50:12,240 --> 00:50:13,520
Idiot.

894
00:50:29,400 --> 00:50:31,000
Would you like these, ma’am?

895
00:50:34,280 --> 00:50:35,280
Yes.

896
00:50:35,440 --> 00:50:37,200
This way, please.

897
00:51:04,440 --> 00:51:05,640
I’m so annoyed.

898
00:51:05,680 --> 00:51:07,640
That was my favorite bracelet.

899
00:51:25,920 --> 00:51:26,920
Si.

900
00:51:31,280 --> 00:51:32,920
Where have you been?

901
00:51:33,200 --> 00:51:34,600
I’ve been looking everywhere for you.

902
00:51:35,000 --> 00:51:36,960
You’re the one who disappeared.

903
00:51:38,560 --> 00:51:39,640
Are you okay?

904
00:51:39,680 --> 00:51:41,920
Why do you look so stressed?

905
00:51:44,720 --> 00:51:45,760
No.

906
00:51:45,760 --> 00:51:47,200
I’m totally fine.

907
00:51:47,800 --> 00:51:48,840
Then...

908
00:51:48,960 --> 00:51:51,640
why haven’t you changed
into the outfit I picked?

909
00:51:52,160 --> 00:51:53,200
Well...

910
00:51:53,200 --> 00:51:54,800
I’m not confident.

911
00:51:55,080 --> 00:51:59,120
I told you I’m taking you to dinner today.

912
00:51:59,360 --> 00:52:00,760
Where are we going?

913
00:52:00,800 --> 00:52:02,480
This outfit is fine, though.

914
00:52:03,840 --> 00:52:06,440
Just go change like I said.

915
00:52:06,480 --> 00:52:08,160
Please, please, please.

916
00:52:16,760 --> 00:52:18,440
Whatever happens, happens.

917
00:52:21,840 --> 00:52:22,840
This way, please.

918
00:52:38,360 --> 00:52:40,400
-Thank you.
-I’ll be back to take your order shortly.

919
00:52:44,560 --> 00:52:45,640
P'.

920
00:52:45,840 --> 00:52:47,120
Are you okay?

921
00:52:48,000 --> 00:52:49,400
Why are you making that face?

922
00:52:50,320 --> 00:52:51,360
Well...

923
00:52:51,440 --> 00:52:54,080
You told me to dress like this,

924
00:52:54,520 --> 00:52:56,600
and do my hair like this,

925
00:52:57,200 --> 00:52:59,520
and come to a place like this.

926
00:53:00,080 --> 00:53:01,280
I’m not used to it.

927
00:53:02,360 --> 00:53:03,560
But today,

928
00:53:03,600 --> 00:53:05,160
you look really beautiful.

929
00:53:07,680 --> 00:53:09,280
I’m sorry.

930
00:53:09,680 --> 00:53:11,760
I was so focused on picking a place I wanted,

931
00:53:11,800 --> 00:53:14,000
I forgot to ask you.

932
00:53:15,120 --> 00:53:16,240
It’s okay.

933
00:53:16,520 --> 00:53:17,800
We’re already here anyway.

934
00:53:18,080 --> 00:53:19,080
I think

935
00:53:19,120 --> 00:53:21,400
trying something new isn’t bad.

936
00:53:21,440 --> 00:53:22,440
Mm.

937
00:53:22,680 --> 00:53:23,880
Let’s order. Come on.

938
00:53:24,600 --> 00:53:25,960
What do we want to eat?

939
00:53:31,800 --> 00:53:32,920
No.

940
00:53:32,920 --> 00:53:35,560
Hey, you have to do it like this.

941
00:53:38,480 --> 00:53:39,520
Yeah.

942
00:53:40,200 --> 00:53:41,240
Here.

943
00:53:55,520 --> 00:53:56,520
Si.

944
00:53:57,480 --> 00:53:58,920
Is the food spoiled?

945
00:54:00,160 --> 00:54:01,200
Let me see.

946
00:54:11,840 --> 00:54:13,240
No, P'.

947
00:54:13,760 --> 00:54:15,680
Really? But I feel like...

948
00:54:15,960 --> 00:54:18,080
the taste is kind of weird.

949
00:54:19,320 --> 00:54:20,960
Spaghetti carbonara

950
00:54:20,960 --> 00:54:22,760
is supposed to taste like this.

951
00:54:23,240 --> 00:54:25,120
Or if you don’t like it,

952
00:54:25,160 --> 00:54:26,520
we can switch plates.

953
00:54:26,520 --> 00:54:27,560
Want to?

954
00:54:31,000 --> 00:54:32,000
Here.

955
00:54:34,360 --> 00:54:36,600
Ta-da.

956
00:54:38,000 --> 00:54:39,840
Australian beef steak,

957
00:54:39,880 --> 00:54:41,000
medium rare,

958
00:54:41,000 --> 00:54:43,200
with gravy sauce.

959
00:54:43,280 --> 00:54:44,880
Try it.

960
00:54:44,880 --> 00:54:45,960
The chef here

961
00:54:46,000 --> 00:54:47,680
is really skilled.

962
00:54:47,720 --> 00:54:49,200
It’s very delicious.

963
00:54:51,280 --> 00:54:52,320
But...

964
00:54:52,440 --> 00:54:54,520
the meat looks undercooked.

965
00:54:54,640 --> 00:54:56,040
Can you really eat this?

966
00:54:56,040 --> 00:54:57,440
Of course.

967
00:54:57,960 --> 00:54:59,360
It’s really good.

968
00:54:59,400 --> 00:55:00,520
Try it.

969
00:55:01,040 --> 00:55:02,640
From the name,

970
00:55:02,680 --> 00:55:04,360
I thought it was some kind of code.

971
00:55:13,400 --> 00:55:14,440
How is it?

972
00:55:15,440 --> 00:55:17,080
It’s good, but...

973
00:55:17,600 --> 00:55:19,760
I think it’s a bit bland.

974
00:55:20,600 --> 00:55:22,120
Can you get me...

975
00:55:22,120 --> 00:55:24,440
some jaew dipping sauce?

976
00:55:24,480 --> 00:55:25,480
What?

977
00:55:27,200 --> 00:55:28,840
Are you serious, P'?

978
00:55:31,120 --> 00:55:32,200
But...

979
00:55:32,680 --> 00:55:34,440
I’m not sure

980
00:55:34,520 --> 00:55:36,040
if they even have that here.

981
00:55:36,960 --> 00:55:39,320
Please, try asking them for me.

982
00:55:39,440 --> 00:55:40,440
Okay.

983
00:55:40,480 --> 00:55:41,480
And...

984
00:55:41,640 --> 00:55:43,920
Besides jaew dipping sauce,

985
00:55:44,200 --> 00:55:45,320
do you want anything else?

986
00:55:45,560 --> 00:55:47,200
Since we’re already asking,

987
00:55:47,240 --> 00:55:50,680
let’s get fresh chili, garlic,
and green onions too.

988
00:55:50,720 --> 00:55:52,640
We can eat them on the side
to cut the richness.

989
00:55:54,600 --> 00:55:55,840
Sure.

990
00:55:58,920 --> 00:55:59,960
Excuse me.

991
00:56:00,200 --> 00:56:01,600
Um...

992
00:56:01,680 --> 00:56:03,040
We’d like jaew dipping sauce,

993
00:56:03,080 --> 00:56:05,680
fresh chili, garlic, and green onions,

994
00:56:05,680 --> 00:56:06,840
please.

995
00:56:07,240 --> 00:56:08,960
Um...

996
00:56:09,040 --> 00:56:11,280
We don’t have jaew dipping sauce here.

997
00:56:12,720 --> 00:56:14,680
Please tell your manager

998
00:56:14,720 --> 00:56:16,080
that Si is requesting it.

999
00:56:16,200 --> 00:56:17,240
Yes, Ms. Si.

1000
00:56:20,480 --> 00:56:21,680
-Si.
-Hmm?

1001
00:56:21,720 --> 00:56:23,360
If it’s too much trouble,

1002
00:56:23,360 --> 00:56:25,000
I can just eat it like this.

1003
00:56:25,040 --> 00:56:26,200
It’s okay.

1004
00:56:26,200 --> 00:56:28,080
This is nothing.

1005
00:56:29,040 --> 00:56:30,640
You know, before,

1006
00:56:30,680 --> 00:56:33,840
I wouldn’t dare say
or do something like this, P'.

1007
00:56:34,000 --> 00:56:35,480
I was afraid people would think

1008
00:56:35,600 --> 00:56:37,160
I’m not classy.

1009
00:56:37,600 --> 00:56:39,680
Then why are you brave now?

1010
00:56:39,720 --> 00:56:41,000
Because of you.

1011
00:56:41,040 --> 00:56:42,440
That’s why I’m brave.

1012
00:56:42,680 --> 00:56:46,280
You make me feel
more confident in myself.

1013
00:56:46,360 --> 00:56:48,720
Especially when I know
I’ve done nothing wrong.

1014
00:56:48,760 --> 00:56:49,760
Right?

1015
00:56:50,920 --> 00:56:51,920
Eat this.

1016
00:56:51,960 --> 00:56:54,560
Try it while we wait for the jaew sauce.

1017
00:56:58,600 --> 00:56:59,680
Here it is.

1018
00:57:00,240 --> 00:57:02,280
Very good.

1019
00:57:03,920 --> 00:57:04,920
Here.

1020
00:57:05,800 --> 00:57:06,840
This.

1021
00:57:09,240 --> 00:57:10,760
Here.

1022
00:57:18,800 --> 00:57:20,040
That’s much better.

1023
00:57:20,040 --> 00:57:21,440
Try it. Come on.

1024
00:57:22,160 --> 00:57:23,640
Here, take this.

1025
00:57:26,680 --> 00:57:27,720
How is it?

1026
00:57:29,800 --> 00:57:30,800
Delicious.

1027
00:57:36,080 --> 00:57:37,080
Perfect.

1028
00:57:37,120 --> 00:57:38,320
Finish your drink, P'.

1029
00:57:38,560 --> 00:57:40,280
All of it.

1030
00:57:46,520 --> 00:57:47,600
Si.

1031
00:57:48,200 --> 00:57:49,680
Give me your hand.

1032
00:57:50,120 --> 00:57:51,160
Why?

1033
00:57:51,360 --> 00:57:53,000
Just give it to me.

1034
00:57:54,280 --> 00:57:55,360
Are you giving me money?

1035
00:58:02,600 --> 00:58:05,360
Did you buy me a bracelet?

1036
00:58:05,920 --> 00:58:08,520
I saw you were upset about losing yours,

1037
00:58:08,560 --> 00:58:10,000
so I got you a new one.

1038
00:58:10,520 --> 00:58:13,160
But I’m not very good
at picking things like this.

1039
00:58:13,160 --> 00:58:15,040
I don’t know if you’ll like it.

1040
00:58:15,040 --> 00:58:16,240
I like it, P'.

1041
00:58:16,240 --> 00:58:17,840
It’s really beautiful.

1042
00:58:17,840 --> 00:58:19,200
It’s way prettier than the old one.

1043
00:58:19,440 --> 00:58:21,040
Thank you, P' Klao.

1044
00:58:25,520 --> 00:58:26,520
Here.

1045
00:58:36,240 --> 00:58:37,240
I think

1046
00:58:37,280 --> 00:58:39,800
I’ll brew you some infused liquor next time.

1047
00:58:39,880 --> 00:58:42,040
Have you heard of “horse-kicking brew”?

1048
00:58:45,920 --> 00:58:47,200
Sure, P'.

1049
00:58:47,440 --> 00:58:49,760
I like trying new things anyway.

1050
00:58:54,320 --> 00:58:56,400
I’m going to the restroom for a bit.

1051
00:58:56,440 --> 00:58:58,760
Okay. Want me to go with you?

1052
00:58:58,800 --> 00:58:59,800
It’s fine.

1053
00:59:48,120 --> 00:59:49,160
Excuse me.

1054
00:59:51,800 --> 00:59:52,800
Are you talking to me?

1055
00:59:53,080 --> 00:59:54,080
Yes.

1056
00:59:54,680 --> 00:59:56,360
What’s your name?

1057
00:59:58,120 --> 00:59:59,200
Why are you asking?

1058
01:00:00,040 --> 01:00:02,200
Can I get your LINE?

1059
01:00:02,880 --> 01:00:05,400
You look just like my ex.

1060
01:00:06,120 --> 01:00:09,240
Seeing you reminds me of her.

1061
01:00:09,640 --> 01:00:12,160
I’m not available.
I already have a fiancée.

1062
01:00:13,880 --> 01:00:15,800
-You.
-Let me hug you.

1063
01:00:15,920 --> 01:00:16,920
Hey.

1064
01:00:17,000 --> 01:00:19,320
-I really miss her.
-You...

1065
01:00:19,360 --> 01:00:21,160
-You look so much like her.
-Let go of me.

1066
01:00:21,200 --> 01:00:23,000
Please, have some sympathy.

1067
01:00:23,000 --> 01:00:25,160
She just died in an accident.

1068
01:00:25,680 --> 01:00:27,800
Please, I’m begging you.

1069
01:00:28,200 --> 01:00:31,800
I’ve never seen anyone
who looks this much like her.

1070
01:00:32,880 --> 01:00:34,400
Can you help me?

1071
01:00:36,280 --> 01:00:38,840
Can I look at your face up close?

1072
01:00:51,080 --> 01:00:52,080
You.

1073
01:00:52,520 --> 01:00:54,640
I miss her so much.

1074
01:00:55,720 --> 01:00:56,720
You.

1075
01:01:33,200 --> 01:01:35,800
You agreed to marry me, right?

1076
01:01:36,800 --> 01:01:37,720
-What?
-What?

1077
01:01:38,520 --> 01:01:40,320
I already told you, Mom,

1078
01:01:40,360 --> 01:01:42,160
I don’t feel anything for her.

1079
01:01:42,600 --> 01:01:44,280
I’m sorry

1080
01:01:44,280 --> 01:01:47,000
that I still don’t have the courage
to tell you the truth.

1081
01:01:47,800 --> 01:01:48,800
Jane.

1082
01:01:52,240 --> 01:01:53,760
You got punched twice

1083
01:01:53,800 --> 01:01:54,880
and still haven’t gone back to Bangkok.

1084
01:01:55,000 --> 01:01:56,640
You’re really stubborn, aren’t you?

1085
01:01:56,680 --> 01:01:58,160
Does she know

1086
01:01:58,240 --> 01:02:00,760
how happy we were together?

1087
01:02:00,800 --> 01:02:02,560
So, how is it? Do you like it?

1088
01:02:07,720 --> 01:02:09,000
It’s fun. I like it.

1089
01:02:09,000 --> 01:02:11,000
I actually like being in nature, but...

1090
01:02:11,040 --> 01:02:13,120
this is a bit too natural.

1091
01:02:13,280 --> 01:02:15,240
(The top is here.)

1092
01:02:15,320 --> 01:02:17,000
She’s so cool.

1093
01:02:17,440 --> 01:02:18,440
Look, look.

1094
01:02:19,680 --> 01:02:20,680
(So serious.)

1095
01:02:20,720 --> 01:02:21,720
It’s my first time.

1096
01:02:21,720 --> 01:02:24,160
It’s not hard, it’s just heavy.

1097
01:02:24,840 --> 01:02:26,560
(Trying so hard.)
The left side has to match.

1098
01:02:26,840 --> 01:02:28,720
(Starting to have fun.)
Hey, are you really driving it?
